items.title: These 3 Dow Jones Stocks Are Crushing It in 2025. Are They Still Buys?
items.author: Keith Speights
items.description: Three Dow Jones stocks - IBM, Amgen, and Coca-Cola - have performed exceptionally well so far in 2025, with gains of nearly 20%, 16%, and 15% respectively. IBM's strong AI business, Amgen's FDA approval and growing free cash flow, and Coca-Cola's impressive dividend streak are the key drivers behind their success.

insights.sentiment_reasoning: IBM's strong performance is driven by its growing AI business, which has a $5 billion book of business, and its ability to potentially benefit from the disruption caused by cheaper AI solutions like DeepSeek.

Amgen's stock has rebounded in 2025 after a decline in 2024, driven by its strong Q4 earnings, double-digit sales growth for 10 of its products, and the FDA approval of its drug Lumakras for treating colorectal cancer.

Coca-Cola's stock has surged nearly 15% year-to-date, putting it near its all-time high. The company's strong Q4 results, market share gains, and its 63rd consecutive annual dividend increase have contributed to this performance.
